abstract: U.S. President Donald Trump has invited British Prime Minister Boris Johnson to visit him in the White House in the new year, British media reported on Sunday.

abstract: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Washington.
snippet: North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Was...
lead_paragraph: SEOUL — North Korean leader Kim Jong Un held a meeting of top military officials to discuss boosting the country's military capability, state news agency reported on Sunday amid heightened concern the North may be about to return to confrontation with Washington.
headline_main: North Korea's Kim Holds Military Meeting as Tension Rises Under Looming Deadline
headline_print_headline: North Korea's Kim Holds Military Meeting as Tension Rises Under Looming Deadline

abstract: MJ Randolph had 16 points and eight rebounds as Florida A&M ended its season-opening nine-game losing streak, defeating Seattle 71-57 on Saturday night.

headline_main: Randolph Scores 16 to Lift Florida A&M Over Seattle 71-57

abstract: Hazardous smoke from bushfires raging over a large swath of eastern Australia have become a headache for the nation's cricket board, which faces the threat of disruptions to its lucrative summer schedule.

headline_main: Bushfires Place Australian Cricket Summer Under Cloud

abstract: Mike Anderson wanted to seal the signature win he's been looking for in his first season as St. John's coach by having Julian Champagnie intentionally miss a free throw to milk the final 0.2 seconds off the clock.

abstract: Corrections that appeared in print on Sunday, Dec. 22, 2019.
snippet: Corrections that appeared in print on Sunday, Dec. 22, 2019.
lead_paragraph: The Ask Watching column last Sunday misstated the location where the television show “Claws” is set. It is in Manatee County, Fla., not Miami. The error was repeated in a picture caption.

abstract: Her send-off for a new jobs included farewell drinks, a round of karaoke and the start of their relationship.

lead_paragraph: Samantha Hindel Meyer and Edward John McGarrigle were married Dec. 21 at Maritime Parc, an events space in Jersey City, N.J. Brian Pramberger, a friend of the couple who became a Universal Life minister for the occasion, led a ceremony incorporating Jewish traditions.
